Installation Guide

* Manual installation

  This package comes as a tar gzip file. After you untar and gunzip the file (tar -zxvf) 

*--------------------------------------------+---------------------------------------------+
|| file                                      || description                               ||
*--------------------------------------------+---------------------------------------------+
| logging.properties                         | set the logging levels                      |
*--------------------------------------------+---------------------------------------------+
| security.properties		                 | required by  the RMI Classloader            |
*--------------------------------------------+---------------------------------------------+
| run.sh		                             | runs the application                        |
*--------------------------------------------+---------------------------------------------+
| run-console.sh                             | runs the application on the console         |
*--------------------------------------------+---------------------------------------------+
| executionservice-0.3.0.jar                 | jar file with application main              |
*--------------------------------------------+---------------------------------------------+
| lib folder                                 | jar dependencies of the application         |
*--------------------------------------------+---------------------------------------------+


 
  If you would like to use the execution service, do the following:

  [[1]] Add -<version>.jar file in your application classpath
  
  
  [[2]] Make sure that following libraries are in your (or made available via the classpath
  
        Refer to the dependencies document for the correct version of these libraries.
        You can download a copy of everything from jakarta or you can grab them from the example webapp in the bin distribution.
        The following is the list of dependencies:

     * commons-logging

     []

* Using maven

 If you use maven 2 for your projects all you need to do is including a reference to displaytag in the dependencies
 section of your POM:

+--------------------------------------------------------------------------+
    <dependency>
      <groupId>org.imirsel</groupId>
      <artifactId>flowservice-api</artifactId>
      <version>0.3.0</version>
    </dependency>
+--------------------------------------------------------------------------+
